SIMPLE: outward
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outward
<hw>Out"ward</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Outward
<hw>Out"ward</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Forming the
superficial part; external; exterior; -- opposed to <ant>inward</ant>;
<as>as, an <ex>outward</ex> garment or layer</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Though our <qex>outward</qex> man perish, yet the inward man is
renewed day by day.</q> <rj><qau>Cor. iv. 16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the outer surface or to what is
external; manifest; public.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Sins <xex>outward</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>outward</qex> honor for an inward toil.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Foreign; not civil or intestine; <as>as, an
<ex>outward</ex> war</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Hayward.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Tending to the exterior or outside.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fire will force its <qex>outward</qex> way.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Out"ward*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Out"ward*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Outward stroke</b></col>. <fld>(Steam Engine)</fld>
<cd>See under <er>Stroke</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outward</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Outward
<hw>Out"ward</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>External form; exterior.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So fair an <qex>outward</qex> and such stuff within.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>outward-bound</ent>⟦br⟧
